

<section>
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        <xref ref="intro-ex-1"></xref>
        There are three given sets
        <m>A=\halmaz{3,4,6,7,8},B=\halmaz{2,4,5,6,8}</m> and <m>C=\halmaz{1,2,4,5,8}</m>. 
        We have that
        <md>
          <mrow>A\setminus B\amp =\halmaz{3,7}</mrow>
          <mrow>C\cap B\amp =\halmaz{2,4,5,8}</mrow>
        </md>.
        Thus
        <me>
          (A\setminus B)\cup(C\cap B)=\halmaz{2,3,4,5,7,8}
        </me>.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        <xref ref="intro-ex-2"></xref>
        We have three sets <m>A=\halmaz{1,3,4,6,7},B=\halmaz{2,4,5,6,8}</m> and <m>C=\halmaz{1,3,4,5,8}</m>.
        <md>
          <mrow>(A\cap B)\amp =\halmaz{4,6}</mrow>
          <mrow>(C\cap B)\amp =\halmaz{4,5,8}</mrow>
        </md>.
        Therefore
        <me>
          (A\cap B)\setminus(C\cap B)=\halmaz{6}
        </me>.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        <xref ref="intro-ex-3"></xref>
        Now the three given sets are
        <m>A=\halmaz{1,3,4,6,7},B=\halmaz{2,4,6,8}</m> and <m>C=\halmaz{1,3,4,8}</m>.
        <md>
          <mrow>(A\setminus B)\amp =\halmaz{1,3,7}</mrow>
          <mrow>(C\setminus B)\amp =\halmaz{1,3}</mrow>
        </md>.
        So we obtain
        <me>
          (A\setminus B)\cup(C\setminus B)=\halmaz{1,3,7}
        </me>.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        <xref ref="intro-ex-4"></xref> (a) The elements of the set are 7, 10 and 13. (b) The elements of the set are 0, 1 and 4. (c) The possible differences are <m>3-1, 3-2, 4-1, 4-2, 5-1</m> and <m>5-2</m>,
        thus the elements of the set are 1, 2, 3 and 4.
      </p>
